VERDICTS  (leakage strength = |attacker_AUC - 0.5| * 2; 0 = oblivious, 1 = perfect leak)
========================================================================
[Branchless / control]
    eager    leakage strength = 0.054  -> no detectable leak
    compiled leakage strength = 0.093  -> no detectable leak
    => No detectable value-dependent timing in either mode.

[Authored branch (torch.cond)]
    eager    leakage strength = 0.802  -> LEAKS
    compiled leakage strength = 0.998  -> LEAKS
    => Leak present in BOTH -> AUTHORED (algorithmic), not compiler-introduced.

Interpretation guide:
  * Large-N Mann-Whitney p-values will often be < 0.05 even when the
    effect is negligible -- trust the AUC/leakage strength, not p.
  * A null result means 'not detectable with this harness', not
    'provably constant-time'. CPU wall-clock timing has a noise floor.
